#!/bin/sh
# rundown launcher (ADR-0001 §4). Prefers an installed compiled binary for this
# platform; falls back to running from source with Bun in the working tree (the
# local-dev path). One entry point, identical invocation in dev and installed.
set -e

# Resolve $0 through any symlinks so an install can symlink this launcher onto
# PATH while still finding src/ (and bin/) in the real working tree.
self=$0
while [ -L "$self" ]; do
  target=$(readlink -- "$self")
  case "$target" in
    /*) self=$target ;;
    *) self=$(dirname -- "$self")/$target ;;
  esac
done
dir=$(CDPATH= cd -- "$(dirname -- "$self")" && pwd)

os=$(uname -s | tr '[:upper:]' '[:lower:]')
arch=$(uname -m)
case "$arch" in
  x86_64) arch=x64 ;;
  aarch64 | arm64) arch=arm64 ;;
esac
binary="$dir/bin/rundown-$os-$arch"

if [ -x "$binary" ]; then
  exec "$binary" "$@"
fi

# Local-dev fallback: run the TypeScript source with Bun.
if command -v bun >/dev/null 2>&1; then
  exec bun "$dir/src/cli.ts" "$@"
elif [ -x "$HOME/.bun/bin/bun" ]; then
  exec "$HOME/.bun/bin/bun" "$dir/src/cli.ts" "$@"
fi

echo "rundown: no compiled binary at $binary and Bun is not installed." >&2
echo "Install Bun (https://bun.sh) to run from source, or install a release binary." >&2
exit 1
